# TaskTrack

This is an Obsidian plug-in for managing tasks.

## Technical Stack
- TypeScript is used instead of JavaScript
- Preact is used for JSX rendering
- Vite is our build system
- Vitest is used for unit testing
- Tailwind is preferred for CSS styling

## Folder Structure

```
tasktrack/
├── src/
│   ├── components/    # UI components (Preact)
│   ├── lib/           # Core library code
│   ├── vendor/        # Third-party code or vendor dependencies
│   ├── worker/        # Web worker implementations
|   |-- **/__tests__/  # Unit tests

## Git Commit Messages
Use conventional commits format:
- `feat(scope): add new feature`
- `fix(scope): resolve bug`
- `docs(scope): update documentation`
- `style(scope): formatting changes`
- `refactor(scope): code restructuring`
- `test(scope): add tests`
- `chore(scope): maintenance tasks`

Where `scope` is the component or area affected (e.g., search, UI, parser).

## Contributing

- Keep PRs focused on a single change or related changes
- For new features, please open a GitHub discussion before or alongside your PR

Before submitting changes:
- Ensure there are no lint errors: `npm run lint`
- Ensure all tests pass: `npm run test`
